This article is a transcript of remarks made by Vice President Mike Pence at a dinner event at the Vice President's Residence in Washington, D.C. The event was held to welcome members of the User Advisory Group, who will be providing advice to the National Space Council. Pence thanked the attendees, including Secretary of the Air Force Heather Wilson and Second Lady Karen Pence. He also acknowledged other members of the Cabinet and government officials present, including Secretary of Commerce Wilbur Ross, Deputy Secretary of State John Sullivan, and Administrator of NASA Jim Bridenstine. Pence emphasized the importance of the User Advisory Group's counsel in advancing the country's space program and collaboration between public and private enterprises. He encouraged the group to bring their best ideas and assured them that their proposals would be considered by the National Space Council. Pence expressed confidence in America's ability to lead in space exploration under the leadership of President Trump and with the expertise of the advisory group.